<b>Subject:</b> Re: Good Riddance to em.......<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1790" TARGET=_self>Good Riddance to em.......</A> (Loren)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> If any one cheats they deserver to be banned and have their ass

<BR>&gt; kicked at the same time. You agree to the terms each time you
<BR>&gt; load the game. If I was running the game I'd have it say in
<BR>&gt; there that actions such as these are punishable by fine and
<BR>&gt; maybe other ways with the law.
<P>Honestly I hate cheaters like I hate the thought of getting cancer. I agree that they should ban each one they can "legitimately re-verify" as using the tool.
<P>As for the punishment by fine they would have to have a county, state, or federal court impose the fine. They can't do it themselves without due-process. Other ways in law may mean that you want to see them dragged before a judge, etc. Unfortunately the agreement you make isn't a binding contract and the only real remedy that the company has is to just ban you. Of course, if the parties sue the company for reinstatement and the judge says that it must be done, there is no recourse other then appeal.
<P>Our system of government, fortunately (although sometimes me thinks not always) functions in the real world and not fantasy role-playing one.
<P>Starcraftor
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
